41.94 vs normal 4,267.32\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"component\": \"frontend-0, frontend-1, frontend-2\",\n      \"reason\": \"Consistent rrt_max degradation across all frontend pods with increases ranging from 1,299,863.5 to 1,490,212.0 (130-136% increases)\",\n      \"evidence\": \"frontend-0: rrt_max 1,359,620 vs 254,257; frontend-1: 1,490,212 vs 281,676; frontend-2: 1,296,863.5 vs 274,311.5\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"component\": \"checkoutservice-2\",\n      \"reason\": \"Error ratio spike with client_error_ratio and error_ratio p99 values increasing from 0.0 to 2.93 (200% increase)\",\n      \"evidence\": \"checkoutservice-2 shows error_ratio p99 from 0.0 to 2.93 and client_error_ratio p99 from 0.0 to 2.93\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n**Key Findings:**\n\n1. **Primary Issue**: The recommendationservice experienced a severe pod-level incident with process explosion (pod_processes increased from 1 to 12 across all pods) and CPU usage spikes.\n\n2. **Cascading Effects**: This caused massive latency increases in recommendationservice-2 (rrt_max up 1,944%) and affected frontend services through dependency chains.\n\n3. **Error Propagation**: The checkoutservice-2 showed error ratio increases, likely due to downstream service degradation.\n\nThe pod_processes anomaly is particularly significant as it indicates potential container restart or process fork issues in the recommendationservice pods, which appears to be the root cause of the performance degradation cascade."}
